OL,3,CWhy this Welsh village celebrates New
OL,4,CYear on 13 January
OL,6,FTime moves slowly in this remote
OL,7,Fvalley in Pembrokeshire.
OL,9,FIn fact, the residents of Cwm Gwaun
OL,10,Fare thirteen days behind the rest of
OL,11,Fus in celebrating the New Year.
OL,13,FNo, they haven't mixed up their dates,
OL,14,Fthis community still celebrates the
OL,15,FNew Year according to the old Julian
OL,16,FCalendar, which was replaced by the
OL,17,FGregorian Calendar in 1752 to fall in
OL,18,Fline with most of Europe.
