OL,3,CWhy this Welsh village celebrates New
OL,4,CYear on 13 January
OL,6,FThe move - which saw Britain and its
OL,7,Fempire skip nearly two weeks overnight
OL,8,F- proved controversial, and
OL,9,Fgenerations of non-compliance means
OL,10,FHen Galan, which is Welsh for "old New
OL,11,FYear", is still celebrated in the
OL,12,FGwaun Valley.
OL,14,FIt sees children walking door-to-door
OL,15,Ffrom dawn til dusk singing traditional
OL,16,FWelsh songs in exchange for gifts
OL,17,Fknown as "calennig".
